SETTING UP A RASPBERRY PI AS AN ACCESS POINT IN A STANDALONE NETWORK
[https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/configuration/wireless/access-point.md]
This tutorial walks through how to set up a Raspberry Pi as a stand-alone access
point to cut out the need to hook the hub up to a router. This may be useful for
development and for deployment. We could incorporate both functionality, assuming
the Raspberry Pi would have limited range, to allow more options for users.

ESPRESSIF - GETTING STARTED WITH THE ESP8266
[https://espressif.com/en/support/explore/get-started/esp8266/getting-started-guide]
This guide goes over the ESP8266 wifi chip and give information on how it works
and how to use it/set it up. 

ADAFRUIT - WHY MQTT?
[https://learn.adafruit.com/mqtt-adafruit-io-and-you/why-mqtt]
This is a good intro guide on the MQTT protocol and why people use it.

MQTT
[http://mqtt.org]
The official source website for MQTT. This has everything from implementation
guides to tutorials to documentation to example projects.
